parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission surge accumulator system can cause the vehicle to lose power, fail to accelerate, and stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate
revs up to high RPMs but fails to reach speed
loses power
and stalls. The check engine light may be illuminated
and the vehicle may display error messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter to communicate to the ECU can cause the vehicle to not recognize when it is in park, leading to safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle displays a "shift to park" message
the dashboard shows the vehicle is in park
but the transmission does not engage
and the vehicle may not turn off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduced engine power can cause the vehicle to lose power, fail to accelerate, and stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle displays a "reduced engine power" message
loses power
and fails to accelerate. The check engine light may be illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the auto start/stop system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off or stalls while driving
the engine light comes on
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and delayed shifting can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
and the engine light may come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Power Reduced and Stabilitrak Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine power reduced and Stabilitrak issues can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine power is reduced
the Stabilitrak light comes on
and the vehicle may lose power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake system failure can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes vibrate or pulse
and the vehicle may not stop properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system malfunction can cause various systems to fail, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical systems
such as the dashboard lights
radio
or wipers
malfunction or fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch and transmission issues can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
and the vehicle may lose power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The "Engine Power Reduced" defect can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to a significant decrease in speed, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways.
symptoms: The "Engine Power Reduced" message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle suddenly loses power
the vehicle slows down to a low speed (around 20-25 mph)
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle stalls or shuts down
and the vehicle may not restart immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft can cause the engine to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine warning light comes on
the vehicle stalls or shuts down
the vehicle loses power
and the "Engine Power Reduced" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The temperature gauge rises
the "Overheating Engine" warning light comes on
and the vehicle overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of critical systems and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
the electrical system shuts down
and the vehicle may not restart immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause the engine to lose power, leading to a decrease in speed and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine warning light comes on
the vehicle loses power
and the "Engine Power Reduced" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift cable adjuster can cause the vehicle to not recognize when it is in park, leading to difficulties in shutting off the engine, which can result in battery drain and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle displays a "Shift to Park" message
the vehicle will not shut off
the vehicle takes multiple attempts to shut off
the vehicle will not recognize when it is in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine reduced power mode can cause the vehicle to slow down significantly, making it difficult to maintain speed, especially on highways, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The "Engine Power Reduced" warning message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle slows down significantly
the vehicle loses power
the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and brake system can cause the vehicle to lose power and braking ability, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal is hard to press
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle slows down significantly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sunroof can cause glass to shatter and fall into the driver's eyes, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The sunroof glass cracks or shatters
the glass falls into the driver's eyes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The error in the Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) can cause issues with the vehicle's history and safety features.
symptoms: The vehicle's VIN is incorrect
the vehicle's history is incorrect.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Reduced Engine Power/Throttle Pedal Position Sensor Correlation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle pedal position sensor can cause the engine power to reduce, leading to a sudden loss of speed, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially on highways.
symptoms: The "Engine Power Reduced" message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle slows down suddenly
the speed is limited to 30-40 mph
the check engine light illuminates
and the traction control light may also come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator pedal mechanism can cause the pedal to fall to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal falls to the floor
making it difficult or impossible to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter or motor can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially on highways.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start
the vehicle shuts off completely when making a complete stop
the vehicle will maintain normal operation if shifted into neutral upon stopping.
